<br>
Nothing  stirred.<br>
<br>
Silence.<br>
<br>
Nothingness.<br>
<br>
Then...<br>
<br>
A candle flickered in a wind that was not blowing.<br>
<br>
Dust motes began to stir in an unfelt breeze.<br>
<br>
The shadows deepened in Aarchus' old room, the door bricked over by the Harvesters who have chosen to strike his name from existence for his betrayal. <br>
<br>
The shadows took on a vaguely man-shaped form, tendrils of shadow-ether trailing behind the entity as it drifted across the vacant space to the desk against the far wall. Faint whispers promised madness from beyond the shroud as the phantasm moved, one-thousand voices whispering as one; over it all one voice stood out among the others:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>I shall live... again... and even you cannot stop me...Father...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
The lost soul began rummaging around in the sheafs of papers in one drawer, tossing aside those that did not fit its dark desires. Finally it produced one piece of vellum triumphantly, if such a creatures of despair and hatred could ever feel such an emotion.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Yessss... to live...again...</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
And suddenly it was gone.<br>
<br>
A cold wind blew through the Halls of the Harvesters that night, snuffing out candles and threatening the hearth-fires in the main hall. Behind this wind, a cackling laughter could be heard... <p>-=Aarchus Xhar'Gothe, the Hand of Innoruuk=-<br>
